outline.en:
1. basics about electric circuits : circuit connection topology, governing physical laws, equations to describe the status of the electric circuits - solving for component status variables - current and voltage drop, electric characteristic equations and parameters of components, fundametal electric components { R, L, C, voltage current sources, dependent sources, diode, transistor, transformer, motor }
2. circuit loops, utility power wiring, grounding, electric shock - hazard of electricution, circuit diagrams of home appliances, electro-magnetic interference, ground loop interference ;
3. solving for circuit status variable functions - using maple symbolic computation tool, system equations for circuit analysis, solve for equivalent circuit parameters, solving for Delta-Y equivalence;
4. accumulation of uncertainties
5. solving for time dependent circuits with RLC components of differencial time dependent characteristics, transient response, Laplace transform, parametric electric circuit design, sine wave driven response - transfer function damping factor adjustment, step response function, AC steady state response, circuit analysis by phasor, frequency response;
6. The electric characteristic v-i curves of a transistor - its h-parameter schematic model, deriving characteristic parameters for the curves, temperature drift of the characteristic v-i curve of a diode, amplifier circuit design - load line design, the Miller capacitor between B and C and its impact on frequency response of the amplifier;
7. difference amplifier circuit design: solve for the frequency response of circuits applying ideal operational amplifier IC;
8. imperfections of the operational amplifier: { temperature drift compensation, nominal operation range }
9. electric circuit characteristics of a DC mortor, power factor adjustment by attach C to the motor;

